🌟 Carefully Balanced Church Website Color Palette
Here’s a custom palette that reflects faith, reverence, growth, energy, and warmth — all in one.

Purpose	Color Name	HEX Code	Use Case
Primary Color	Deep Blue	#1E3A8A	Header, navbar, footer background (trust, depth)
Secondary Color	Forest Green	#2E7D32	Buttons, highlights (growth, creation)
Accent Color	Warm Gold	#FFD700	Icons, CTA buttons, scripture highlights (spiritual glow)
Background Color	Off-White	#FAFAF9	Main background (clean, readable)
Text Color	Charcoal Gray	#333333	Paragraphs, body text (clear & modern)
Highlight Color	Soft Coral	#FF6F61	Section headers, youth pages, events (friendly, warm)

🎯 Example Section-by-Section Usage
🧭 Navigation Bar:
Background: #1E3A8A (Deep Blue)

Links: #FFFFFF (white)

Active link / hover: #FFD700 (Gold)

🏠 Page Background:
#FAFAF9 (Off-White) — light and breathable

📝 Text:
Main body: #333333 (Charcoal)

Headings: #1E3A8A or #2E7D32

Scripture quotes: #FFD700

📣 Buttons:
Primary (CTA): Background #2E7D32, Text #FFFFFF

Secondary: Background #FF6F61, Text #FFFFFF

👣 Footer:
Background: #1E3A8A

Text: #FFFFFF

